     <font class="TallRed">The outcome of the recent DevlogikSymbiot meeting.<a name="108744389894254610">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          I'm going to make this very short so I can make like horsecrap and hit the hay. The E3R team met up tonight and discussed some of the issues that needed to be addressed: comments on E3R posts, new handling of E3R Applications, and other stuff that you don't really give a poop about. Here are the results.<br /><br /><strong>Comments:</strong> while comments are not being taken out of posts, they ARE being defaultly disabled. Every post will be able to have the comment capability but the author of the post must click on "More Posting Options" and select that commenting on that specific post is allowed. This will keep <i>some</i> of the problems at bay. Cless and I are going to work on instructions on balance between Blogging and Commenting but basically it goes a little like this: Look pal, if your comment is more than 4 lines in length, you need to BTFU and post it. <a href="http://www.blogger.com/profile/3563019">Need help with instructions on how to contribute anonymously?</a> <br /><br /><strong>E3R Application Handling:</strong> all members of E3R should try to look for other new possible posters to keep the spirit alive around here. All Applications sent in till this point have been accepted majorly because these accounts were writers for E3R before. Now, we have just about all of our old posters back and there are some new people who are asking for access. These will need time to process because instead of just copying an email address and sending an invite, the application is forwarded to every member of DLS where I wait for an OKAY or a NOKAY (just made that word up. funny? yes?).<br /><br />As far as everything else, its still up in the air. We may be porting to a new posting system people. I'm sure you're going to be so happy over that. Comments are welcome, but post responses are too.<br />
